The Social Democratic Party (SDP) has elected Barr. Natasha Akpoti as the party’s candidate for the November 16 governorship election in Kogi State. The party’s primary election which held at the Kafas Multi-purpose hall, Lokoja, was witnessed by officials of the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC). Daily Trust reports that 856 delegates from across the 21 local government areas of the state voted for Akpoti who was the sole aspirant in the contest. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY The returning officer for the primary, Mr Ben Ogbonna, from the National Secretariat of the party declared Natasha Akpoti as the duly elected SDP governorship candidate. In her post-election speech, Akpoti thanked the delegates for the confidence reposed on her and pledged to turn around the fortune of the state if elected. Kogi: Women group buys SDP form for Natasha Akpoti Kogi Guber: Natasha Joins race, promises to reposition economy Kogi: Female senatorial candidate pledges resuscitation of Ajaokuta, NIOMCO Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin